{
  "stem": "18770.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 381.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't think it would-- worked-- you know, I mean, it was not used every day or every week, but on special holidays, it functioned as a shul.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, my-- there were four floors to this house, with an elevator, which was a big deal in Poland prior to World War II.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Every one of the floors had two apartments, and on each floor, one of my uncles and aunts and their children-- occupants.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So there were four families directly part of the Lax family that occupied each floor.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were on the top floor.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my-- the other four apartments were rented out to other tenants.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I-- when I saw-- I've never been back there, and I've-- I've heard that the house was completely-- it wasn't destroyed because Cracow was an open city.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In other words, it wasn't bombed during World War II, unlike Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The house was not destroyed, but I think it was completely re-- you know, changed and remodeled and redone.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So all I had were these childhood memories of me playing in this fairly luxurious and what seemed to me very large apartment that I lived in with my mother, father, and my sister.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then when I saw there's a scene in the movie where Schindler takes over an apartment that used to belong to wealthy Jews that he's provided with an apartment by the Nazis, you know.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I said, my God, that's our apartment.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The shape of it-- the shape of the rooms-- that rectangular look of those rooms.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Just absolutely, just it was amazing to see it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very nice.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] No, it was.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was-- I don't remember the-- the specific, exact, you know, setup of every day.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Here are some of the memories I have.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
